    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Creamware that is lead-glazed, and originating ca. 1763. It was developed by Josiah Wedgwood and named after Queen Charlotte. Its popularity eventually led to the disappearance of the English, tin-glazed earthenware industry. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
